<br>
2) In your discussion of tons of aluminum plating, I think it is important for you to clarify your use of &quot;nuclear engine&quot;.<br>
<br>
Altho an external nuclear pulse engine, expending tons of fissiles and kilotons of propellent may have no problem with massive shields, that is not the case with &quot;conventional&quot; nuclear engines. Their Isp's are typically within 1 order of magnitude of a chemical engine - which would provide zero benefit if massed up with metal.<br>
<br>
yale<br>
